    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-04T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-04T09:00:00-05:00" n="671"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d671">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-04T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 4, 1954—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 374. Repeated information Saigon 142,
                    Paris 384. <persName corresp="#p_NDK1">Dac Khe</persName> told <persName
                        corresp="#p_HDR1">Heath</persName> yesterday that he had protested to French
                    delegation that French Officers, who have now started talks in Geneva with
                    representatives of Viet Minh command, are defeatists. Vietnamese Government has
                    Colonel <persName corresp="#p_LVK1">Kim</persName> sitting in on these talks and
                    Vietnamese delegation has added <persName corresp="#p_TVT1">Tran Van
                        Tuyen</persName>, both of whom have been instructed watch for any signs of
                    “defeatist concessions” by their French colleagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
